WEBVTT

01:20.914 --> 01:22.498
MIKE:
All your equipment's missing too.

01:22.666 --> 01:25.960
They took everything.
You think it's the kids from Lakeland High?

01:26.128 --> 01:27.378
I don't know, Mike.

01:29.548 --> 01:32.800
Someplace with a good
art department, apparently.

01:35.721 --> 01:37.013
You don't think your kid...?

01:37.181 --> 01:39.515
What? Damon? No, Mike.

01:39.683 --> 01:41.684
I was just thinking, you know...

01:41.852 --> 01:44.145
...the pissing and the... Never mind.

01:44.354 --> 01:45.855
[SIGHS]

01:46.482 --> 01:47.523
You okay?

01:47.691 --> 01:51.569
No, Mike. No, I am not okay.

01:51.737 --> 01:53.821
There's nothing left, Mike.
Don't you get it?

01:53.989 --> 01:57.366
The whole state has nothing left.

01:57.534 --> 02:00.077
- That's it.
- We have the alumni game.

02:00.537 --> 02:01.913
What?

02:02.456 --> 02:03.956
The alumni game.

02:04.124 --> 02:05.750
We can raise a little money there.

02:05.918 --> 02:09.253
Mike, we don't have the equipment
to play in the alumni game.

02:09.421 --> 02:11.005
We'll borrow from East Lansing.

02:11.173 --> 02:15.009
Look, I know we don't usually make a lot,
but if you actually played this year...

02:15.177 --> 02:17.845
...it could make a big difference.
It'll boost morale too.

02:18.013 --> 02:22.558
I don't know. I feel weird going out there
like I'm still 18. I'm the manager now.

02:22.726 --> 02:24.936
People don't want
to see you manage, Ray.

02:25.103 --> 02:28.815
People want to see you hit the ball.

02:30.317 --> 02:31.609
RAY:
The alumni game.

02:31.777 --> 02:34.070
I hadn't played it for nine years.

02:34.530 --> 02:36.447
When people think you're hot shit...

02:36.615 --> 02:38.407
...all you can do is disappoint them.

02:38.575 --> 02:41.369
I guess I didn't want to come up short.

02:42.079 --> 02:43.371
[GRUNTING]

02:48.377 --> 02:50.127
Oh, look at those two.

02:50.295 --> 02:54.340
Oh, they're in love.
Seals are very romantic.

02:55.050 --> 02:57.718
- They are?
- Absolutely.

02:57.886 --> 03:01.389
Seals form long-lasting
romantic relationships.

03:01.557 --> 03:04.016
I take a field trip here every year.

03:04.184 --> 03:05.476
Seals are my favorite.

03:05.644 --> 03:07.937
Sensitive and strong.

03:08.105 --> 03:10.523
So you really teach?

03:10.691 --> 03:12.859
Of course. It's all I've ever done, really.

03:13.026 --> 03:14.861
And coach.

03:15.112 --> 03:17.113
You coach? You really do that?

03:17.281 --> 03:19.282
Thirty-two years. I love it.

03:19.449 --> 03:21.701
We're having our
alumni baseball game Saturday.

03:21.869 --> 03:23.452
You should come if you want.

03:23.620 --> 03:25.454
I'm not much at the plate these days...

03:25.622 --> 03:28.958
...but I can still field
with the best of them.

03:29.126 --> 03:31.043
I'm thinking... I was hoping actually...

03:31.753 --> 03:33.170
Uh...

03:33.338 --> 03:35.631
You could buy a block of tickets.

03:35.799 --> 03:37.049
We usually have sponsors...

03:37.217 --> 03:40.803
...but, you know, sponsors these days
have mostly evaporated.

03:41.263 --> 03:44.557
Mike, I'm sorry, I don't know
what you're asking me.

03:45.559 --> 03:47.852
To maybe consider supporting the team.

03:48.020 --> 03:50.271
To buy a block of tickets for the game.

03:50.439 --> 03:52.231
It doesn't have to be a lot.

03:52.399 --> 03:55.318
You could write a check for whatever.

03:57.195 --> 03:58.779
You want me to write you a check?

03:58.947 --> 04:00.948
Whatever feels right.

04:01.450 --> 04:03.910
- They're good kids, you know.
- Oh.

04:04.828 --> 04:07.580
No obligation, but it's...

04:07.748 --> 04:10.917
- It's hard for schools these days.
- Mm.

04:13.337 --> 04:14.754
You think I'd spray-paint...

04:14.922 --> 04:17.423
...two wolves fucking each other
in your locker room?

04:17.591 --> 04:21.427
Just forget I said anything.

04:23.972 --> 04:25.932
So are you coming
to this game Saturday?

04:26.099 --> 04:29.685
I peed on home plate, Dad.
I'm not a vandal.

04:30.437 --> 04:32.146
I'm going to the salad bar.

05:35.043 --> 05:37.253
Mind if I try some?

05:37.504 --> 05:41.048
May I have a bite of your
enchiladas verdes?

05:41.216 --> 05:44.135
- You said you weren't hungry.
- I'm not.

05:46.179 --> 05:48.514
Mmm. Mm.

05:48.807 --> 05:51.726
That is delicious. Delicious.

05:51.893 --> 05:54.020
Especially when it's free, right?

05:54.187 --> 05:56.105
Everything tastes better
when it's free.

05:56.273 --> 05:58.065
I don't know what
you're talking about.

05:58.233 --> 06:00.901
All right, Frances,
Mike was at your house on a Wednesday.

06:01.069 --> 06:03.529
That's a weekday.
You booked him for the weekend.

06:03.697 --> 06:05.656
You only paid me for the weekend.

06:05.824 --> 06:08.576
He brought me breakfast unannounced.

06:08.744 --> 06:10.619
Was I supposed to say no?

06:10.787 --> 06:12.621
I thought maybe it was included.

06:12.789 --> 06:14.623
Why would you say no?
No, you want Mike.

06:14.791 --> 06:16.959
Unlimited access, unlimited hours.
That's fine.

06:17.127 --> 06:19.837
No, we just... We have to renegotiate.

06:22.466 --> 06:24.425
I'm thinking...

06:26.011 --> 06:28.304
...something along...

06:28.889 --> 06:30.473
...these lines.

06:31.850 --> 06:33.350
I can't possibly pay that.

06:33.518 --> 06:35.603
You can say yes. You can say no. Okay.

06:35.771 --> 06:37.897
But if you say no, then I have no choice...

06:38.065 --> 06:41.317
...to call Mike
and terminate your relationship.

06:49.117 --> 06:50.159
Okay.

06:50.327 --> 06:52.912
Will you just give me
my payment for this week?

06:53.080 --> 06:55.372
What are you people doing to me?

06:55.540 --> 06:58.501
Mike asked me for money
and I paid him. And now you're...

06:58.668 --> 07:01.796
Wait, wait, wait.
You gave money to Mike?

07:01.963 --> 07:04.090
He asked for it, okay?

07:04.674 --> 07:08.344
Or, I don't know, I think he asked for it.

07:08.512 --> 07:13.015
All right, Frances,
I think Mike was confused.

07:13.183 --> 07:15.392
So why don't...? You know what?

07:15.560 --> 07:16.977
Just write me a check.

07:17.145 --> 07:20.898
I'm a person, not an ATM machine.

07:21.066 --> 07:22.316
[STAMMERS]

07:22.484 --> 07:25.528
Ours is a mutually beneficial arrangement.

07:25.695 --> 07:28.405
It's... We're like... It's like those birds...

07:28.573 --> 07:30.741
...that live on a hippo and eat bugs.

07:33.370 --> 07:35.746
I don't think I can handle this.

07:39.334 --> 07:43.796
I'm not going to see Mike again.

07:46.133 --> 07:48.425
You're despicable.

07:51.721 --> 07:54.932
Yeah, hi, Charlie. I need to talk to you.
It's important.

07:55.100 --> 07:56.767
I'm trying to make my own rules...

07:56.935 --> 07:59.019
...but then I just don't...

07:59.187 --> 08:00.896
I don't... I'm just...

08:01.064 --> 08:03.858
I'm not feeling in a very
pimp state of mind right now.

08:05.193 --> 08:07.486
RAY:
Most players don't get the perfect ending.

08:07.654 --> 08:10.990
They spend their last couple of years
hurt, injured.

08:11.158 --> 08:13.033
They fade into oblivion.

08:13.451 --> 08:16.078
But they never give up looking for it.

08:23.879 --> 08:25.838
RAY:
So how's it going?

08:27.507 --> 08:30.092
This is how it's going.

08:30.510 --> 08:33.053
I live in this tub.

08:33.221 --> 08:35.931
Because it's the only place
that makes me feel comfortable.

08:36.600 --> 08:40.269
I sit here with my boobs
growing like watermelons.

08:40.437 --> 08:42.438
And my back is fucking killing me.

08:42.606 --> 08:46.483
And I only leave to go eat chili cheese fries
at chain restaurants.

08:46.651 --> 08:48.194
I don't bring my phone in here...

08:48.361 --> 08:51.572
...I'm afraid of dropping it in the water
and electrocuting my baby.

08:51.740 --> 08:55.201
My best friend's afraid to come over
because last time I screamed at her...

08:55.368 --> 08:57.953
...for no fucking reason whatsoever.

08:58.496 --> 09:00.789
I guess I'm Ionely.

09:03.084 --> 09:04.501
Still no Peter?

09:05.587 --> 09:07.504
Still no Peter.

09:08.173 --> 09:10.049
I'm glad he's gone.

09:10.634 --> 09:14.845
I don't even know why I called you.
I'm too fat to fuck.

09:18.600 --> 09:20.768
I think you look great.

09:21.436 --> 09:23.312
A little pregnant.

09:24.272 --> 09:25.856
But beautiful.

09:31.696 --> 09:33.072
What?

09:35.075 --> 09:36.867
I'm a professional.

09:40.330 --> 09:41.372
[CLAIRE GIGGLES]

09:56.596 --> 09:57.763
I missed you, Richard.

09:59.891 --> 10:01.225
I missed you too.

10:03.395 --> 10:04.812
Oh, God.

10:07.190 --> 10:10.484
No one has done this to me
in a long time. Just this.

10:12.654 --> 10:14.780
Third base.

10:17.575 --> 10:19.285
Kiss me.

10:25.250 --> 10:26.917
Oh, God, this is...

10:27.085 --> 10:28.585
This is really hot.

10:28.753 --> 10:30.421
Keep going.

10:30.588 --> 10:31.839
[BOTH GRUNTING]

10:33.174 --> 10:35.759
Keep going. Keep going. Keep going.

10:37.887 --> 10:39.263
[YELLS]

10:40.140 --> 10:42.266
[BOTH YELLING]

10:48.231 --> 10:50.065
[RAY GROANING]

10:52.235 --> 10:54.403
Oh, God.

10:54.571 --> 10:56.113
Are you okay?

10:56.281 --> 10:59.325
- It's my shoulder.
- What happened?

10:59.492 --> 11:03.620
I have a rotator cuff thing.

11:04.998 --> 11:06.623
Did you come?

11:07.417 --> 11:09.084
Yeah.

11:09.919 --> 11:11.378
[CLAIRE LAUGHING]

11:14.966 --> 11:17.092
- Jess?
- Ron.

11:17.260 --> 11:19.470
Wasn't it locked? I thought it was locked.

11:19.637 --> 11:21.180
What is that?

11:21.348 --> 11:22.556
Oh, it's old.

11:22.724 --> 11:25.142
- Old what?
- Just nothing.

11:25.310 --> 11:27.561
- Well, let me see it.
- It's no big deal.

11:27.729 --> 11:29.980
It's absolutely unimportant.

11:31.941 --> 11:33.525
Okay, fine. Jeez, Ron.

11:34.110 --> 11:36.487
I have a rash, okay? It's just a little rash.

11:36.654 --> 11:39.865
I didn't want to bother you with it,
so I dug up some old cream.

11:40.033 --> 11:41.742
I think everything's gonna be fine.

11:41.910 --> 11:44.995
Jess, what's going on?
I'm one of the top skin men in Detroit.

11:45.163 --> 11:47.498
If you had a rash,
why didn't you just come to me?

11:49.125 --> 11:53.003
I just didn't want you to get upset.

11:53.171 --> 11:56.382
Honey, rashes do not make me upset.

11:56.549 --> 11:58.592
Cars do not make mechanics upset.

11:58.760 --> 12:00.761
Hair does not make beauticians upset.

12:00.929 --> 12:03.931
I know my way around a rash.

12:04.224 --> 12:06.058
Okay, Ron.

12:07.352 --> 12:09.395
Here's my rash.

12:11.940 --> 12:13.273
Oh.

12:19.697 --> 12:22.533
3 YEARS AGO

12:24.536 --> 12:26.245
Ow. Oh!

12:27.163 --> 12:28.205
- Ray.
- What?

12:28.373 --> 12:30.165
Ray, look at this.

12:31.584 --> 12:33.377
Ray, it's getting worse.

12:33.545 --> 12:35.754
Could you just get the ointment, please?

12:40.593 --> 12:42.511
You should go back to that dermatologist.

12:42.679 --> 12:45.013
I did. He said the cream
isn't gonna cure it.

12:45.181 --> 12:47.015
All the allergy tests
came back negative.

12:47.183 --> 12:50.894
- He thinks it's psychosomatic.
- What?

12:51.062 --> 12:53.272
He says it's my body's way
of saying, "Help."

12:53.440 --> 12:55.190
The dermatologist said this?

12:55.733 --> 12:59.862
Dr. Haxon is very well-respected.
He knows what he's talking about.

13:02.574 --> 13:05.451
Don't you want to know
why I'm unhappy?

13:05.618 --> 13:07.578
You're unhappy?

13:10.582 --> 13:12.583
That rash.

13:13.501 --> 13:14.960
Yeah.

13:16.463 --> 13:17.588
[RAY GRUNTS]

13:17.755 --> 13:19.214
How does it feel?

13:19.382 --> 13:21.133
It's not good. It's not good.

13:21.301 --> 13:23.719
Is it a tear or an inflammation?

13:23.887 --> 13:25.679
I don't know. I think it's a tear.

13:26.306 --> 13:28.307
What happened?
You were casting and...?

13:28.475 --> 13:31.602
- Yeah.
- There's no downward thrust in fishing.

13:31.769 --> 13:33.604
Yeah, it's a mystery.

13:33.771 --> 13:35.689
It's not even the same muscles.

13:36.483 --> 13:39.067
Let it go, Mike. I can't play.

13:39.235 --> 13:41.445
Oh, just one inning in the field.

13:41.613 --> 13:44.198
Everyone's coming back, Ray.
Everyone is gonna be there.

13:44.365 --> 13:46.950
I can't do it. I can't throw.

13:47.118 --> 13:50.204
- You could play first base.
- I gotta pee.

13:50.705 --> 13:54.208
Maybe I'll pee on home plate like my kid.

13:56.920 --> 13:58.629
The grass feels good.

14:00.882 --> 14:02.382
What?

14:02.675 --> 14:05.677
I'm an idiot. I fucked up.

14:07.096 --> 14:09.723
- What are you talking about, Mike?
- I should kick myself.

14:09.891 --> 14:14.853
I asked Frances to sponsor the team,
like an idiot.

14:15.271 --> 14:18.148
- And I guess she thought...
- What?

14:18.316 --> 14:19.983
I don't know.

14:20.944 --> 14:22.194
Something.

14:22.362 --> 14:24.821
She got upset about money.

14:25.782 --> 14:28.158
Now she won't call me back.

14:32.080 --> 14:36.708
I fucked it up like I always do, Ray.

14:36.876 --> 14:40.003
Why do I always fuck it up?

14:49.472 --> 14:50.847
[KNOCKS]

14:51.558 --> 14:52.724
[SIGHS]

14:53.560 --> 14:56.520
- It's late.
- Hi.

14:57.689 --> 15:03.277
I'm sorry. I'm sorry I banged Lenore.

15:05.947 --> 15:09.616
- So, what happened?
- It's my shoulder.

15:10.034 --> 15:14.079
You know, when you hurt yourself,
you're supposed to RICE.

15:14.247 --> 15:15.289
Rice?

15:15.456 --> 15:20.919
Yeah, rest, ice, compression, elevation.

15:21.087 --> 15:22.212
You wanna RICE me?

15:28.136 --> 15:31.263
Thanks, Ray, for saying
"I'm sorry" about Lenore.

15:32.640 --> 15:35.475
Did you give the money back to Frances?

15:36.436 --> 15:37.894
What?

15:38.062 --> 15:40.272
Did you give the money back to Frances?

15:41.899 --> 15:44.985
Yeah, Ray.
You told me to give it back to her...

15:45.153 --> 15:47.863
...so I went over to give it back.

15:49.115 --> 15:52.993
I wouldn't lie to you, Ray.
I wouldn't do that to you.

15:53.995 --> 15:58.457
Okay.

16:00.084 --> 16:01.126
MAN:
Yeah, good stuff.

16:02.879 --> 16:04.129
[MEN LAUGHING]

16:04.297 --> 16:05.631
[BARKING]

16:11.346 --> 16:17.184
- I was rather hoping to see you play today.
- Yeah, me too. But I injured myself.

16:18.311 --> 16:20.979
MIKE:
The fact is, Frances...

16:23.066 --> 16:27.653
I love you. And that's how I feel.

16:28.404 --> 16:31.448
I hope you call me back.

16:32.700 --> 16:34.785
I gotta go play
a baseball game now, okay?

16:34.952 --> 16:36.495
MAN:
All right, guys, let's circle up.

16:36.663 --> 16:38.622
- Come on, Drecker.
- You all right?

16:38.790 --> 16:41.708
MAN: Put your hands in.
- All right, fellas.

16:41.876 --> 16:43.251
On three, fellas. Ready?

16:43.419 --> 16:46.046
One, two, three!
Wolf pack, wolf pack!

16:46.506 --> 16:48.423
Whoo!

16:50.009 --> 16:52.177
[GIRL SINGING NATIONAL ANTHEM]

17:13.533 --> 17:15.117
[CROWD CHEERING]

17:19.539 --> 17:21.039
Yeah!

17:24.043 --> 17:27.003
ANNOUNCER [OVER PA]:
Thank you. And welcome, Wolves alumni.

17:27.171 --> 17:29.214
Okay, I'll pick you guys up at 9.

17:29.382 --> 17:31.466
Why do we have to go? You're not going.

17:31.634 --> 17:34.886
Because it's your dad,
and baseball is his life.

17:35.054 --> 17:37.556
- Was his life.
- You're going and that's it, okay?

17:37.724 --> 17:40.559
Think about somebody
other than yourself for once.

17:44.397 --> 17:46.857
Here, buy some hot dogs.

17:54.532 --> 17:57.951
GIRL 1: Go, wolf pack!
GIRL 2: Go, wolf pack! Whoo!

18:05.209 --> 18:06.752
Whoo!

18:07.545 --> 18:08.795
[CROWD CHEERING]

18:17.180 --> 18:20.474
ANNOUNCER:
And that's two runs scored by the students.

18:20.641 --> 18:23.101
RAY:
We wanted to win. Nobody said it.

18:23.269 --> 18:27.439
"It's all for the team. It's all in good fun,"
blah, blah, blah. Bullshit.

18:27.607 --> 18:29.858
We wanted to win.

18:30.026 --> 18:33.278
We wanted our lives to be ahead of us.

18:55.635 --> 18:56.760
[GASPS]

18:56.928 --> 18:58.261
Damon.

18:58.429 --> 19:01.097
- Hi.
- Hi.

19:01.516 --> 19:02.682
You're here for the game?

19:03.726 --> 19:05.977
Game? What game?

19:06.145 --> 19:08.480
Oh, the baseball game.

19:10.441 --> 19:12.442
No, I don't watch baseball.

19:12.985 --> 19:14.319
So, what are you doing here?

19:14.904 --> 19:17.072
It's complicated.

19:20.493 --> 19:22.244
I'm here to confess a crime.

19:23.204 --> 19:24.246
Is everything okay?

19:27.124 --> 19:28.750
No.

19:30.253 --> 19:32.379
Everything is...

19:33.381 --> 19:34.923
...not okay.

19:36.217 --> 19:38.802
Ray, can I talk to you for a sec?

19:39.846 --> 19:41.930
I'm kind of busy here, Ronnie.

19:42.223 --> 19:44.057
Shouldn't be out here.
What do you need?

19:44.225 --> 19:45.767
Jessica has a rash.

19:47.770 --> 19:50.272
- Hey, good swing.
ANNOUNCER: That's strike one.

19:50.439 --> 19:52.983
You want me to go to the store
and buy her some cream?

19:53.150 --> 19:54.734
I want you to stay away from her.

19:54.902 --> 19:55.986
Excuse me?

19:56.153 --> 19:59.573
She picked me. She left you for me.

20:00.283 --> 20:02.325
She picked me too, Ron.

20:02.493 --> 20:04.536
But now she's allergic to you, Ray.

20:04.704 --> 20:07.622
She was allergic before,
but now that you keep coming around...

20:07.790 --> 20:09.332
...she's breaking out in hives.

20:10.751 --> 20:12.711
Did you ever think, Ron...

20:12.879 --> 20:14.379
...maybe she's allergic to you?

20:14.547 --> 20:17.173
ANNOUNCER: Strike two.
- Fuck you.

20:17.466 --> 20:19.259
You never noticed guys like me.

20:19.427 --> 20:22.721
But now guys like me,
we rule the fucking world.

20:25.224 --> 20:26.558
ANNOUNCER:
Strike three.

20:32.565 --> 20:35.650
WOMAN:
Let's go, alumni! Come on!

20:54.545 --> 20:56.546
[CROWD SINGING UPBEAT SONG]

20:59.300 --> 21:00.800
[RAY GRUNTING]

21:45.513 --> 21:48.473
LAMBERT:
Hey, coach, you suited up?

21:48.641 --> 21:52.352
- Yeah, I'm gonna give it a shot.
- But you're hurt.

21:52.520 --> 21:55.105
Well, buddy, listen.
Even if I wasn't hurt...

21:55.272 --> 21:57.732
...I don't think I could take you,
so don't worry.

21:57.900 --> 22:00.944
Well, a high fastball
might be coming your way.

22:01.445 --> 22:03.863
- What?
- Third pitch, coach. Nobody will know.

22:04.031 --> 22:06.533
Lambert, no.

22:12.206 --> 22:13.456
One, two, three, four.

22:13.624 --> 22:17.043
Go alumni!

22:17.712 --> 22:19.004
MAN 1:
Let's do it!

22:20.006 --> 22:22.340
Ronnie, what are you doing here?

22:22.508 --> 22:24.926
- I'm... I'm going.
ANNOUNCER: Now batting...

22:25.094 --> 22:27.262
Are you coming with me
or are you staying here?

22:27.430 --> 22:30.807
...coach Ray Drecker.
- Mom, Dad, he's playing.

22:30.975 --> 22:32.350
[CROWD CHEERS]

22:33.978 --> 22:38.565
Ron, honey, it's just a game.

22:48.284 --> 22:50.243
ANNOUNCER:
Now batting, Ray Drecker.

22:53.539 --> 22:56.374
- Go, Dad!
- Let's go, Ray.

22:58.878 --> 23:03.965
RAY: When I was 18, did I ever think
I'd be here, playing where I grew up?

23:04.133 --> 23:06.843
With all these faces I'd known all my life?

23:10.681 --> 23:11.806
They'll never know.

23:12.516 --> 23:16.436
There's a lot of things
they'll never know about me.

23:18.105 --> 23:20.315
UMPIRE: O and two.
ANNOUNCER: Strike two.

23:20.483 --> 23:22.317
MAN 2:
You've got one more.

23:22.485 --> 23:25.695
DARBY: You can do it.
- This is it. Come on, Ray!

23:25.863 --> 23:27.405
MIKE:
Come on, Ray, baby, let's go.

23:27.573 --> 23:29.991
MAN 2:
Come on, you've got one more.

23:30.326 --> 23:33.995
MIKE: Come on, Ray, let's go. Get it right.
Let's get it right, bud.

23:43.464 --> 23:47.258
RAY: And then there it was,
a little high and a little away...

23:47.426 --> 23:51.763
...just the way he said it was gonna be.
And I couldn't resist.

23:54.141 --> 23:55.767
That beautiful feeling...

23:55.935 --> 23:58.394
...when the ball connects
in just the right spot...

23:58.562 --> 24:00.897
...just the right place.

24:01.440 --> 24:05.193
And you don't even have to look.
It's gone.

24:12.952 --> 24:15.870
We were never gonna win,
but it didn't matter.

24:16.038 --> 24:18.873
I watched the ball fly,
and I watched it fade.

24:19.041 --> 24:21.376
And everything stopped.

24:29.385 --> 24:31.553
As home grew closer
and my team waited there...

24:31.720 --> 24:34.264
...for me to cross the plate, I realized...

24:34.431 --> 24:38.768
...that my shoulder
was fucking killing me.

24:40.271 --> 24:41.688
[CROWD CHEERING]

24:45.901 --> 24:47.026
Whoo!

24:58.455 --> 25:00.290
[MIKE SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

25:01.917 --> 25:04.169
Whoa, whoa. Wait, wait.

25:05.254 --> 25:07.005
Hi.

25:07.381 --> 25:09.215
I'm so glad you came.

25:12.553 --> 25:15.138
Mike, I think it's time...

25:15.306 --> 25:17.182
...that we just spoke like adults.

25:17.725 --> 25:22.812
Tanya and I agreed that
we wouldn't speak about money, but...

25:22.980 --> 25:24.647
Who's Tanya?

25:25.441 --> 25:28.902
Tanya, the woman I pay to see you.

25:30.571 --> 25:32.488
You pay someone to see me?

25:34.783 --> 25:36.117
Oh, you mean the dating service?

25:37.494 --> 25:39.704
Mike, stop pretending.

25:40.831 --> 25:42.707
I'm not pretending anything.

25:45.169 --> 25:46.502
Look.

26:12.905 --> 26:15.114
- That was some kind of hit, Ray.
- Aw.

26:16.242 --> 26:18.576
You should have cheered.
It would have been fun.

26:18.744 --> 26:21.371
There's no cheering in baseball.

26:23.832 --> 26:25.541
Let's see this.

26:31.257 --> 26:33.925
DARBY: Hey, nice hit, Dad.
- Thanks.

26:34.093 --> 26:37.303
- Yeah, it was sort of epic, I guess.
- Epic, huh?

26:37.471 --> 26:39.138
DARBY:
Can we get pizza on the way home?

26:39.306 --> 26:41.641
- Yeah, sure.
- But first your mom's gonna do us a cheer.

26:41.809 --> 26:44.519
DARBY: What?
- No, I'm not. I just told you that...

26:44.687 --> 26:47.605
DARBY: Are you joking?
- You just told me how excited you were.

26:47.773 --> 26:50.275
- Let's see what you got.
- Actually, yeah, here you go.

26:50.442 --> 26:52.735
DAMON: Do it.
RAY: Prove you still got it, lady. Prove it!

26:52.903 --> 26:55.738
- Not here. What are you doing?
RAY: It's your turn.

27:02.371 --> 27:03.788
Ready.

27:04.415 --> 27:05.873
Okay.
